modules.description: This module provides a sleep operation that blocks the current thread for a specified duration in nanoseconds. It works with integer values representing time intervals and returns a promise that resolves after the delay. Use it to implement precise timing delays in asynchronous workflows, such as rate limiting or timed retries.

This module combines system-level timing operations with precise sleep functionality to manage asynchronous workflows. It exposes abstract time values and operations to retrieve the current time or sleep for a given duration, often used in network services and system tasks. The sleep operation, provided by its child module, allows delaying execution in nanosecond intervals, returning a promise that resolves after the specified delay. You can use it to implement timed retries, rate limiting, or coordinated delays in concurrent operations.
